    "long_instructions": "### Getting started with a backtrack\r\n\r\nA backtrack is a pre-made audio track that plays during a live performance to add extra layers of sound. It supports the live musician by providing a beat, harmony, or atmosphere while they perform and add new elements in real-time.\r\n\r\n**Do this:** \r\n- Create a simple backtrack with at least one drum and one bass sound played together. \r\n- Loop that backtrack so it plays for at least 30 measures. ",
